<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 4:16PM PDT  by NWS Pendleton</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Umatilla and west central Union Counties through 445 PM PDT...
At 415 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hilgard, or 12 miles west of La Grande, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hilgard and Kamela.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
